==English==
===Noun===
# mountain range in West Asia, between Black Sea and Caspian Sea, on territory of Russia, Georgia, Armenia and Azerbaijan. Highest peak Elbrus, 5633 m.
===Usage Note===
Usually as '''the Caucasus'''
===Quotations===
*'''1851''': the long and rugged ravines of '''the Caucasus''' &mdash; Lieutenant Maturin Murray, ''The Circassian Slave, or The Sultan's Favorite'', 1851
*'''1895''':Germany, Italy, Spain and Belgium writhed in the throes of Anarchy, while Russia, watching from '''the Caucasus''', stooped and bound them one by one. &mdash; Robert W. Chambers, ''The King In Yellow'', 1895